    <reference type="string">&lt;p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: HPSimplified, Arial; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"&gt;To configure email when you are not connected to the HP network (connect to my Exchange mailbox using HTTP):&lt;br style="box-sizing: border-box;"/&gt;&lt;br style="box-sizing: border-box;"/&gt;RPC over HTTP allows you to access your email from outside of HP using Outlook.&lt;br style="box-sizing: border-box;"/&gt;&lt;br style="box-sizing: border-box;"/&gt;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;Manual Configuration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: HPSimplified, Arial; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Open Outlook.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Click the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;File&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;tab in the upper left corner of your window.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Click&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;Account Settings&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;tab&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;and then click&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;Account Settings&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;from the collapsible menu&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Click the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;Email&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;tab.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Click&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Change&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Click More Settings.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Click the Connection tab.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Under Outlook Anywhere, select the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;Connect to Microsoft Exchange using HTTP&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;check box.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		To specify a proxy server, click&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;Exchange Proxy Settings&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		In the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;Use this URL to connect to my proxy server for Exchange&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;field, type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;sync.com&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Check the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;Mutually authenticate the session when connecting with SSL&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;box.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		In the&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principal name for proxy server&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;field, type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;msstd:sync.hp.com&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		In the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;Use this authentication when connecting to my proxy server for Exchange&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;field, select&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;NTLM Authentication&lt;/strong&gt;. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Click&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;OK&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;three times.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Click&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;Next&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Click&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;Finish&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		Restart Outlook.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;
		When Outlook opens, you may be prompted with the logon credentials box. Enter your&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;domain\username&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;password&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;(e.g. americas\johncitizen).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: HPSimplified, Arial; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"&gt;&lt;strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;Note:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;the password prompt is normal when using RPC over HTTPS and may appear frequently, depending on your version and configuration of Outlook. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</reference>
